    Ember.UI.ProgressBar
    <small>
      <strong>&#123;&#123;progress-bar&#125;&#125;</strong>
    </small>
  </h1>
</div>
<p>
  Horizontal progress bar that fills from left-to-right.
</p>


<hr />
<h3>Usage</h3>

<h4>Binding</h4>
<div class="well" style="background: #FFF">
  {{progress-bar percentBinding="controllerProgress"}}
</div>
<p>
  Most commonly a progress bar is bound to a controller property that will increase from 0 to 100.
  Use <code>percentBinding</code> with the name of the controller property.  If that property isn't
  initially set, is not a number, etc. it will be 0.  Decimals are OK.
</p>
<pre>&#123;&#123;progress-bar percentBinding="propertyName"&#125;&#125;</pre>
<br/>

<h4>Explicit</h4>
<div class="well" style="background: #FFF">
  {{progress-bar id="progressBar" percent="60"}}
</div>
<p>
  It is also possible to explicitly set the progress bar's completion percentage to anything
  between 0 and 100.
</p>
<pre>&#123;&#123;progress-bar percent="60"&#125;&#125;</pre>
<pre>progressBar.set('percent', downloaded / totalSize);</pre>


<hr />
<h3>Appearance</h3>

<h4>Styles</h4>
<div class="well" style="background: #FFF">
  <table width="100%">
    <tr>
      <td width="70" style="vertical-align: top">default</td>
      <td style="valign: top">{{progress-bar percent="20"}}</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="vertical-align: top">success</td>
      <td>{{progress-bar style="success" percent="40"}}</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="vertical-align: top">warning</td>
      <td>{{progress-bar style="warning" percent="60"}}</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="vertical-align: top">danger</td>
      <td>{{progress-bar style="danger" percent="80"}}</td>
    </tr>
  </table>
</div>
<p>Use the <code>style</code> property to change the color.</p>
<pre>&#123;&#123;progress-bar style="success"&#125;&#125;</pre>
<br/>

<h4>Animated</h4>
<div class="well" style="background: #FFF">
  <table width="100%">
    <tr>
      <td width="70" style="vertical-align: top">animate</td>
      <td style="valign: top">{{progress-bar animate="true" percent="20"}}</td>
    </tr>
  </table>
</div>
<p>
  Use the <code>animate</code> property to add motion to the progress bar.  Great for letting the
  user know the app hasn't frozen.
</p>
<pre>&#123;&#123;progress-bar animate="true"&#125;&#125;</pre>
